{
  "stem": "12289.2",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So, he went on to the bitter end, you know, and so on.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, he was, of course, restricted at the beginning.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because Horthy had according-- after the appeal from the Swedish King Gustaf V, had stopped all the-- all the deportations from Budapest.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So first, Eichmann had no possibility to act.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What he had did-- what he had done, already, of course, already starting in-- in March, was when he-- he evacuated the whole countryside, when he brought 600,000 Jewish people to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So when Wallenberg comes, it's-- it's a concentration then on our-- on our part, to try to save at least as many Jewish people in Budapest as possible.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had this favorable climate to start with, when Horthy had to stop the deportations.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So during that time, Eichmann couldn't do very much.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But then comes the new situation, after the revolution on the 15th of October, when Horthy tried to jump the ship.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the-- the Germans immediately reacted and deported him to Germany and gave all the power to the Hungarian-- to the Hungarian Nazis.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then comes this-- the situation with negotiations with Eichmann, trying to-- to stop him to go on then and all that.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At-- I-- that was left to Wallenberg.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You see, we had this-- this sort of organization.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We had a traditional Swedish embassy, with my boss, the ambassador, who was already, at that time, 65 years old.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he was going to retire.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But he volunteered and stayed on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The other ambassadors, the other-- other embassies, they-- they just left.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They-- they-- they didn't stay on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, they were-- I-- I won't say they were a coward, but anyhow, they-- they-- they left.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
